example.eg: I will complete the painting by Friday.
example.egtrans: 我将在星期五以前画完这幅画。

example.eg: The collection was complete with the acquisition of the final missing book.  This is the complete trilogy.
example.egtrans: 买到所缺的最后一本书后，收藏就完整了。这是完整的三部曲。

trans_examp.trans_cn: 完全的, 完整的, 充分的

example.eg: Is that project complete, or is it still going?
example.egtrans: 那个项目完成了吗？或者还在进行之中？

trans_examp.trans_cn: 全面完成的, 结束的

example.eg: The war caused the complete destruction of the city.
example.egtrans: 战争导致了城市的彻底破坏。

trans_examp.trans_cn: 完完全全的, 彻底的

example.eg: He was a complete professional, able to do anything asked of him.

dsense.name: complete⇒
dsense.guideword: UK (finalize house purchase) (购房手续最后一步)

example.eg: Our house purchase fell through a week before we were due to complete.
They completed the fundraising, having reached their target.

trans_examp.trans_cn: 全部完成, 结束, 完全达到

example.eg: The Yankees completed a sweep of their Boston opponents.
example.egtrans: 洋基队大获全胜，击败了对手波士顿队。

example.eg: We have exchanged contracts, and are due to complete the house purchase next week.
example.egtrans: 我们交换了合同，约定下周完成房屋购买。

trans_examp.trans_cn: 全血细胞计数, 血常规

example.eg: The man's complete and utter confusion was obvious from the look on his face; I don't think he had a clue what I was talking about.

trans_examp.trans_cn: 一片茫然, 不知所云, 被完全搞糊涂

example.eg: The prankster shouted "Fire!", which threw the crowd into complete and utter confusion.
example.egtrans: 恶作剧的人大喊 "着火了！"，让人群陷入极度混乱当中。

trans_examp.trans_cn: 极度混乱, 完全无序, 混乱不堪

example.eg: You can't possibly have provided a complete answer with such a short response.
Please state your answers in complete sentences.
